
:INFO
How Aquaponics Works
Fish produce ammonia-rich waste. Beneficial bacteria in the grow bed convert that \
ammonia first into nitrite and then into nitrate, which plants absorb as fertilizer. \
The plant roots clean the water, which flows back into the fish tank. The system \
becomes self-regulating once the bacterial colony is established, usually within \
3 to 4 weeks of startup.

